  <td valign=3Dtop style=3D'padding:0cm 5.75pt 0cm 5.75pt'>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DSpellE>Phaerax</span> are tall slim cr=
eatures
  with a sandy coloured exoskeleton. The <span class=3DSpellE>Phaerax</span>
  resemble the various flora on their home planet <span class=3DSpellE>Phae=
ros</span>
  and have a curious way of moving which emulates the various plants under
  different weather conditions. <br>
  <br>
  On their home planet the <span class=3DSpellE>Phaerax</span> evolved to
  camouflage themselves from the many giant predators. The giant <span
  class=3DSpellE>Draxis</span> Lizards that would hunt on the wind were the
  biggest threat to the <span class=3DSpellE>Phaerax</span> and other simil=
ar
  sized insects. The <span class=3DSpellE>Draxis</span> only exist in zoos =
now,
  hunted to extinction in the wild. <br>
  <br>
  On <span class=3DSpellE>Phaeros</span> most creatures have the natural ab=
ility
  to transmit radio waves of different frequencies to communicate, but some
  creatures such as the <span class=3DSpellE>Phaerax</span> have developed =
the
  ability to transmit micro waves with their own body to cook their food an=
d to
  kill. Exceptional warriors the <span class=3DSpellE>Phaerax</span> are de=
adly
  in close quarters. <br>
  <br>
  <span class=3DSpellE>Phaerax</span> don't make reliable allies although t=
hey
  will often appear friendly to the strong or where it helps them because t=
he <span
  class=3DSpellE>Phaerax</span> have a natural strong motivation to ensure =
they
  are on the winning side. <br>
  <br>
  They live in glass tunnels under the sand, having become masters at drill=
ing <span
  class=3DSpellE>under ground</span>. Since they have become a lot more self
  sufficient due to technology the <span class=3DSpellE>Phaerax</span> only=
 go to
  the surface to maintain farms for the various creatures they eat, preferr=
ing
  to spend their time with the least solar exposure.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The <span class=3DSpellE>Phaerax</span> prefer Beam =
and
  Bombardment Weapons with a Balanced approach to Energy Research.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>For game pla=
y the <span
  class=3DSpellE>Phaerax</span> want to aggressively take up as much Desert
  Colonies as they can. They also need to consider they want to have the mo=
st
  troops compared to their enemies so the <span class=3DSpellE>Phaerax</spa=
n> are
  likely to ally with who they think to be strong.<o:p></o:p></i></p>
